theorem Topology.interior_frontier_eq_empty_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (A := A) → interior (frontier A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  intro hP1
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (frontier A) ⊆ ∅`
    intro x hxInt
    -- `x` is also in `frontier A`
    have hxFront : x ∈ frontier A := interior_subset hxInt
    -- From `P1`, we know `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`
    have hClosSub :=
      Topology.closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
    -- Hence `frontier A ⊆ closure (interior A)`
    have hFrontSub : frontier A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      intro y hy
      exact hClosSub hy.1
    have hxClosInt : x ∈ closure (interior A) := hFrontSub hxFront
    -- Choose an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` contained in `frontier A`
    rcases hxInt with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUSub⟩
    -- Density of `interior A` in its closure yields a point of `interior A` in `U`
    have hNon : ((U ∩ interior A) : Set X).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClosInt U hUopen hxU
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hyIntA⟩⟩
    -- But `U ⊆ frontier A`, contradicting `frontier A` ∩ `interior A` = ∅
    have hyFront : y ∈ frontier A := hUSub hyU
    have hFalse : False := hyFront.2 hyIntA
    exact (hFalse.elim)
  · -- `∅ ⊆ interior (frontier A)`
    exact Set.empty_subset _
